For Koreans, I guess its okay.  But for people who know what authentic Greek food tastes like, this place is very bland.  The meat wasnt marinated or seasoned at all for both dishes.  Im used to dill, onion, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper seasoning.  I even like hints of lemon and lime.  The sauces were good, the roasted vegetables were nice, and the presentation was decent.  Ill have to keep trying other spots.

Would give zero stars if I could.

Cafe has a policy that each person has to order one drink each. So we did.

Its a crime to sell their special milk tea for $7 when it tastes of condensed milk with no hint of tea taste.

The pancakes are average at best. Nothing special. Dont get how they pride themselves as a pancake specialty place.

Did they get so many good reviews because of the $1 discount customers get when they do a review? Id rather miss out on that dollar and do everyone a favour instead.

If youre a tourist or a local in the area, it would be wise to use your money and calories on something better.

In response to seller:
The owner has seemed to have missed the point. Our main critique stems from the taste of the food and drinks. We understand cafes policy to have 1 drink per person. Each cafe has its own rules. None of the other google reviews seemed to have highlighted this, so we wanted to.

Tasty drinks would have done the policy justice. Unfortunately with the current quality of their milk tea, customers cannot be helped but feel like they have been forced to waste $7 to purchase a subpar drink.

Seller says the milk foam may not have suited my taste buds, but I beg to defer. The tea tasted nothing like tea, but tasted like condensed milk diluted in water instead.

Very very disappointed with this place. I was super excited to eat some donkatsu and hadn't eaten all day to save up my appetite for here. Me and my husband waited an hour to be seated here. When we finally got seated we gave our order to the server and waited patiently. This place only had about 7 tables and while we were waiting other families got seated after us. After about 20 minutes of sitting I finally got my order but noticed my husband's food didn't come. That's when the server told us we had to wait about 10 minutes for his meal and then left. The families that came after us were ALL served their meals before my husband's even came. I didn't want to eat without my husband so after waiting and watching everyone get served my food naturally turned cold. I finally had enough and just got up and left. Terrible terrible service. They forgot my husband's food and didn't even make it a priority to bring it out or make it up  to us. Never coming here again. And it such a shame, this place aesthetic was very nice.

This is a traditional Korean pub with a rustic feel, reminiscent of an old tavern.

As a Korean-style restaurant, everything from the interior to the food evokes the atmosphere of an old tavern.

??Famous Noodle Soup with Crispy Rice
This is the signature dish of Kwakyol Restaurant, featuring a small whole chicken and plenty of crispy rice in a pot that comes with a burner to keep the soup boiling hot while you eat.

As you eat the delicious meat, the crispy rice absorbs the broth and turns into a tasty porridge.

Even if you don't order rice, this hearty and savory noodle soup will satisfy your appetite.

??Squid and Chive Pancake
Despite the inclusion of "chive" in the name, it's not spicy at all. It's a large pancake that's cooked until crispy, more like a savory snack than a pancake. It's very crunchy with every bite.

On top of the pancake are finely chopped squid and chives. The combination of the crispy pancake and the savory squid and chive is very tasty, but the price of 20,000 won (approx. $17 USD) may seem a bit expensive.

Even on weekdays at 7 p.m., the place is so popular that there is a waiting list, but the wait time is not as long as expected, perhaps because people tend to drink alcohol as well.

If you're looking for a cozy Korean pub in Yeonnam-dong, we recommend Kwayo Restaurant.

??Kwayo Restaurant
??225-13 Yeonnam-dong
??Fri, Sat 5 p.m. to 2 a.m.
??Sun-Thu 5 p.m. to 1 a.m.
??Last order 1 hour before closing
??Famous Noodle Soup with Crispy Rice: 25,000 won (approx. $21 USD)??
??Squid and Chive Pancake: 20,000 won (approx. $17 USD)"
